
[1]ultramarine

   ULTRAMARINE, a. [L. ultra, beyond, and marinus, marine.]

   Situated or being beyond the sea.

                          ULTRAMARINE, n. [supra.]

   1. a beautiful and durable sky-blue; a color formed of the mineral
   called lapis lazuli, and consisting of little else than oxyd of iron.

   2. Azure-stone.

   Ultramarine ashes, a pigment which is the residuum of lapis lazuli,
   after the ultramarine has been extracted. Their appearance is that of
   the ultramarine, a little tinged with red, and diluted with white.
